HEADWORD: Melanaemia
<hw>Mel`a*nae"mi*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>me`las</grk>, <grk>me`lanos</grk>, black + <grk>a"i^ma</grk>
blood.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A morbid condition in which the
blood contains black pigment either floating freely or imbedded in the
white blood corpuscles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

